Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cairo - An Egyptian court sentenced four men on Wednesday to death by hanging for the 2011 killing of a Coptic Christian priest in his apartment in the southern city of Assiut, state news agency Mena reported.The four were found guilty of killing Reverend Dauoud Peter Boules during a robbery that was aided by his maid, Mena said. The men beat and stabbed the priest to death and stole his money and some belongings.There did not appear to be a political or religious motive behind the crime, a security source told Reuters. One of the four convicted is Christian, the source said.One of the four was tried in absentia, while a fifth man was sentenced to 10 years in prison for assisting in the crime, Mena said.Death penalties in Egypt are rarely carried out. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.